description: The topmost manuscript is titled: 'Our Glorious King Who is Bold and Not That Racist' by John Quillmaster.

name: Delivery: Geomantic Surveys
description: You leaf through the stack of papers. You realize you don't find rocks particularly interesting. You put the papers down...

name: Delivery: Mortar
description: The kind you build walls with. It's pretty heavy.

description: Big wooden boxes, mainly for the shipment of solid goods.

description: Big wooden barrels, mainly for the shipment of liquids, grains and the like.

description: Someone has stitched "NOT TOO B THRON IN RIVAR" on the side.

name: Delivery: Old Clothes
description: A big pile of old clothes, barely used. Probably fashionable once upon a time.

name: Delivery: Farmyard Tools
description: Tools suitable both for shoeing hooves and preparing delicious cheese-based dishes.

name: Delivery: Assassination Order
description: Order for the assassination of a key enemy figure. Comes with the Royal stamp.

name: Delivery: Casualty Report
description: Lists all the casualties experienced by a unit in the past week. There's quite a lot...

name: Delivery: Regimental Rings
description: Rings used to identify military leaders who otherwise could not be identified after battle.

name: Delivery: Medical Supplies
description: A large quantity of military-issue medical supplies. Somebody is expecting trouble...

name: Delivery: Sensitive Barrels
description: The warnings plastered all over the outside make it abundantly clear that these barrels do not contain anything mundane. The cumulative effect of all the instructions is that they should not be touched, moved or looked at, ever.

name: Arena Sigil

name: Moose

name: Direwolf
description: One of Albion's fastest mounts, the Direwolf specializes in hunting, pursuit, and evasion.

name: Elder's Transport Mammoth
description: What a mammoth lacks in speed, it makes up for in enormous carrying capacity. Mammoths are the favored transport of anyone wishing to move really, really large quantities of goods.

name: Elder's Command Mammoth
description: Battle Mount - This war mammoth's command platform allows its rider to direct and bolster allies. Immune to crowd control.

name: Flame Basilisk
description: Battle Mount - This mount can breathe fire on enemies and ignite them from a distance. Immune to displacement effects.

name: Venom Basilisk
description: Battle Mount - This armored mount can lunge at enemies and poison them. Immune to displacement effects.

name: Siege Ballista
description: Battle Mount - Immune to displacement effects.

name: Spectral Bonehorse
description: Secret rituals allow the spirit of an ancient knight's mount to animate the cooling corpse of a sacrificial horse. Loyal and obedient, its appearance nevertheless strikes fear into its foes.

name: Swiftclaw
description: Keeper scouts have used these fast animals to scout the wilds and will never surrender a cub willingly.

name: Rageclaw
description: The fastest and most aggressive Swiftclaw cubs are raised as Rageclaws: battle mounts for berserker cavalry. Raised from birth to tolerate the fury of battle, Rageclaws deliver their riders right into the heart of the enemy ranks.

name: Morgana Nightmare
description: Every Morgana horse-breeder dreams of birthing a foal angry and aggressive enough to survive demonic possession. The resulting creature is almost as dangerous to its rider as it is to its enemies.

name: Spring Cottontail
description: Spring Cottontails are only found during the Rites of Spring. They're very fast companions, but can grow extremely irritable without a strict diet of chocolate.

name: Caerleon Cottontail
description: The Dreaded Rabbit of Caerbann...Caerba...Caerleon. You were warned to only feed it chocolate, but did you listen? Oh, it's just a harmless little bunny, isn't it?

name: Yule Ram
description: Mount - With this mount you can celebrate the Midwinter Festival

name: Avalonian Basilisk
description: A Swamp Dragon infused with Avalonian Energy. Can discharge energy to escape from attackers.

name: Recruiter's Saddled Bat
description: Referral Mount - Can fly on its own, though with a human on top it becomes too heavy to fly over obstacles.

name: Recruiter's Giant Frog
description: Mount - Her name is Berta. Born in a backwater swamp, she dreams of someday seeing the world.

name: Expert's Warhorse
description: An armored horse bearing the impressive banner of its rider's guild. Ideal for raising morale in big battles.

name: Pest Lizard
description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - Quick and hard to catch, this baleful creature can emit intoxicating poison when threatened.

name: Snow Husky
description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - A very good sprinter with a positive and loyal attitude towards humans.

name: Frost Ram
description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - This mount's skillful leap makes it hard to catch.

name: Saddled Terrorbird
description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - These animals like to toy with humans, but once trained become very fast and reliable companions.

name: Grizzly Bear
description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - A strong animal that can easily carry a lot of weight. Its mighty presence alone strikes fear in any attackers.

name: Black Panther
description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - A real hunter, very swift with the ability to temporarily sprint at high speed to catch any prey.

name: Morgana Raven
description: The disciples of Morgana seem to worship this fascinating animal and will likely consider riding it to be heresy.

name: Gallant Horse
description: A heavy horse, also known as Cold Blood. Fearless and not easily impressed by any unforeseen threats.

name: Spectral Direboar
description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - Neither burden nor death can stop this beast, which walks in two worlds at once.

name: Divine Owl
description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - A being bestowed with divine wisdom and the gift of clairvoyance.

name: Heretic Combat Mule
description: Adventurer's Challenge Reward - An abomination of war that could only have been contrived by the most perverted of minds.

name: Keeper Symbol
description: A symbol commonly used by the Keepers to mark their territory.

name: Keeper Flag
description: A Keeper flag which is commonly used to mark their territory.

description: The more powerful Keepers tend to mark their lairs with the bones of animals they have killed to show their strength.

name: Keeper Star of Power
description: The Keeper druids sometimes imbue the very ground they stand on with magical power to amplify their own.

name: Keeper Fire Bowl
description: A mysterious glowing oil is inside this bowl. It is probably safer to not try drinking from it.

name: Keeper Cauldron
description: A big cauldron used by the Keepers to cook their meals and hang their meat over to give it a nice smoky flavor.

name: Keeper Rock Fireplace

description: The Heretics aren't known for their skill in construction.
